    <para id="id11011466">ENGLISH HOME LANGUAGE</para>
    <para id="id11011470">Grade 4</para>
    <para id="id12898902">CHILDREN LIKE ME</para>
    <para id="id6622723">Module 12</para>
    <para id="id6622727">I AM WHO I AM</para>
    <para id="id7879199">All over the world children like you live their lives and have hopes and dreams. Just like you they want to be loved and educated and treated with respect. Children everywhere have the right to healthcare, education, food, shelter and play. And above all, they have the right to be protected against violence.</para>
    <para id="id9203979">These rights are contained in the United Nations Convention on the Rights of the Child, which nearly every country in the world has accepted. Your country has accepted this Bill of Rights. This document is yours and it makes sure that your voice (and all children’s voices) is heard and that you have the right to be happy and enjoy life as much as you can.</para>
    <para id="id6704730">Activity 1</para>
    <para id="id6704733">To do simple research work to find information [LO 5.2.3]</para>
    <para id="id8133337">CHALLENGE</para>
    <para id="id13123958">Find out about UNICEF and its emblem. Write what UNICEF stands for and paste or draw its emblem.</para>
    <para id="id6692246"/>
    <para id="id9606053"/>
